Lectures give overview about different approaches to culture: 
1) ontological
2) anthropological
3) sociological
4) esthetical
5) hermeneutical
6) postcolonialist
7) posthumanist
8) phenomenological (incl. emobodied knowledge)
10) semiotic and communicativeObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide general overview of the selected theoretical approaches to culture and its communication in the context of social and humanist fields - their history, philosophical and methodological sources, central terms and concepts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the students should: - have the overview of the selected approaches of theories of culture, its key-concepts, methods and authors; - is able to read significant texts in critical manner and apply the gained knowledge on his/her own academic and creative practices.
